      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. This chassis has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including a VANOS system refresh and rear subframe reinforcement to ensure long-term structural rigidity. The suspension geometry remains tight, providing the communicative feedback E46 enthusiasts demand. Mechanically robust and ready for the canyons, this M3 offers a pure, naturally aspirated performance profile.",
